    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-11T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-11T08:00:00-05:00" n="691"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60 f 12A/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-11T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Minister of Foreign Affairs spoke to me about the draft of treaty of
                    arbitration transmitted by you to the Czechoslovak Minister at Washington on
                    March 27 ultimo. He is prepared to sign this as it stands but would prefer to
                    substitute [for?] the word “equity” in article one, first paragraph, last line,
                    the words “international law” as equity conveys a different connotation under
                    their law. He does not however insist on this. He is willing to sign such a
                    treaty either at Prague or at Washington in accordance with your preference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
